Package: autoMR
Type: Package
Title: Automated Mendelian Randomization Workflows and Visualizations
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    c(
      person("Kelin", "Zhong", email = "kelin.zhong@uconn.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
      person("Chia-Ling", "Kuo", email = "kuo@uchc.edu", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Provides tools to summarize, analyze, and visualize results
    from Mendelian randomization studies using summarized genetic
    association data. The package includes functions for generating forest
    plots and scatter plots at the level of single-nucleotide
    polymorphisms (SNPs) and Mendelian randomization methods, and for
    fitting multiple estimators in a unified workflow, including
    inverse-variance weighted estimation, MR-Egger regression, the
    weighted median estimator, robust adjusted profile score (RAPS),
    Mendelian randomization pleiotropy residual sum and outlier
    (MR-PRESSO), Mendelian randomization with the genotype recoding
    invariance property (MR-GRIP), and MR-Horse. Related methods are
    described in Burgess et al. (2013) <doi:10.1002/gepi.21758>, Bowden
    et al. (2015) <doi:10.1093/ije/dyv080>, Bowden et al. (2016)
    <doi:10.1002/gepi.21965>, Zhao et al. (2020)
    <doi:10.1214/19-AOS1866>, Verbanck et al. (2018)
    <doi:10.1038/s41588-018-0099-7>, Dudbridge et al. (2025)
    <doi:10.1371/journal.pgen.1011967>, and Grant and Burgess (2024)
    <doi:10.1016/j.ajhg.2023.12.002>. Related open-source software
    includes TwoSampleMR <https://github.com/MRCIEU/TwoSampleMR>,
    mr.raps <https://github.com/qingyuanzhao/mr.raps>, MR-PRESSO
    <https://github.com/rondolab/MR-PRESSO>, and MR-Horse
    <https://github.com/aj-grant/mrhorse>.
